  "prompt": "Can I take modafinil with adderall?",
  "response": "Combining modafinil and Adderall can lead to increased stimulation and may amplify side effects like anxiety, increased heart rate, and elevated blood pressure. Both medications are used to treat different conditions\u2014modafinil is primarily prescribed for narcolepsy and other sleep disorders, while Adderall is used for attention deficit hyperactivity disorder (ADHD) and narcolepsy.\n\nIt's crucial to consult with a healthcare provider before combining these medications. They can provide personalized advice based on your health history and current medications. Always follow your provider's guidance when it comes to medication use.",
